---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={desc} site={site} path={path}>
  <ArticleSchema title={title} description={desc} siteName={site.name} domain={site.domain} path={path} />
  <section class="relative overflow-hidden py-16 md:py-24">
    <div class="container">
      <a href="/use-cases" class="link text-sm">← Use-case playbooks</a>
      <span class="badge mt-6">Marketing stack playbook</span>
      <h1 class="hero-title mt-5 max-w-5xl">Shopify marketing stack for {useCaseName}</h1>
      <p class="mt-7 max-w-3xl text-xl text-cyan-100">{heroSubtitle}</p>
      <p class="mt-5 max-w-3xl text-lg text-slate-300">Trigger: {trigger} · Timing: {timing}</p>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="container pb-12">
    <TldrBox title={`Stack picks for ${useCaseName}`} picks={tldrPicks} />
    <article class="prose-shopify mb-12 card">
      <h2>Stack execution playbook</h2>
  <p>Holiday gifting is a stack coordination peak — not a single campaign blast. Gift buyers, self-purchasers, VIPs, subscribers, and wholesale accounts need different message types in the same four-week window. Without collision calendar and segment priority rules, subscribers receive gift guide, replenishment reminder, and 30% BFCM promo same afternoon.</p>
  <p>Gift guide emails launch 4 weeks before primary holiday — segmented by category (for him, for her, under $50) from Privy gift-intent capture tags. Self-purchasers on replenishment flows suppress gift messaging unless they opt into gift guide separately.</p>
  <p>Shipping deadline urgency is the highest-converting gift email type — dynamic cutoff dates by shipping zone from Shopify or carrier API. Sequenzy branches: still-arrives-by-Christmas vs express vs too-late-show-gift-card.</p>
  <p>Gift card last-minute option saves revenue after physical cutoff — prominent module in Dec 18–23 sends. Digital delivery instant; design distinct from physical product templates.</p>
  <p>Jewelry and high-AOV gift paths emphasize arrival certainty and gift packaging — not deepest discount. Financing and gift receipt options in email two.</p>
  <p>SMS for shipping deadline final 48h — Postscript or Omnisend to opted-in gift buyers who clicked guide but did not purchase. One SMS per holiday season per subscriber cap.</p>
  <p>Yotpo gift-appropriate reviews and UGC in gift guide modules — unboxing photos outperform spec sheets for gift confidence.</p>
  <p>Loyalty tier early gift guide access for VIP — 48h before general list. Suppress loyalty points pitch during gift deadline week — focus on arrival.</p>
  <p>Subscriber box brands: gift subscription offer separate branch from subscriber renewal preview — collision kills both if combined.</p>
  <p>International markets: suppress gift emails when regional shipping cutoff passed — geo segment required.</p>
  <p>Post-holiday: gift purchasers enter thank-you and Jan self-purchase nurture, not immediate winback discount.</p>
  <p>Analytics: gift revenue attribution, gift card sales from email, shipping tier conversion, return rate on gift purchases.</p>

      <h2>Merchant scenarios</h2>
  <p><strong>Jewelry Q4:</strong> Privy gift quiz → Sequenzy guide by recipient → deadline series by zone → gift card module Dec 20+. No lead discount.</p>
  <p><strong>Beauty gift sets:</strong> Bundle gift sets in guide; subscriber suppressions; Yotpo gift wrap UGC; SMS Dec 21 cutoff opt-in only.</p>
  <p><strong>Food corporate gifting:</strong> B2B tag for corporate bulk — separate from consumer gift guide. MOQ and delivery date in template.</p>
  <p><strong>Home decor:</strong> Large item shipping deadline prominent; room gift guide segments; extended return policy module for gift purchases.</p>
  <p><strong>Pet gift buyers:</strong> Gift guide by pet type; self-purchaser replenishment suppressed; cute UGC modules.</p>
  <p><strong>Digital gift cards only:</strong> Last-minute Dec 23–25 email series; no shipping modules; instant delivery CTA.</p>

      <h2>Stack checklist</h2>
      <ul>
    <li>Gift vs self segments defined with mutual suppressions</li>
    <li>Shipping deadline dynamic content tested per zone</li>
    <li>Gift card module live before physical cutoff passes</li>
    <li>VIP early access 48h before general gift guide</li>
    <li>Subscriber renewal and gift subscription on separate calendar rows</li>
    <li>Wholesale/B2B excluded from consumer gift promos</li>
    <li>International geo suppressions after regional cutoff</li>
    <li>SMS deadline cap one per subscriber per season</li>
    <li>Replenishment flows paused or branched for gift season</li>
    <li>Return policy gift-specific module in post-purchase</li>
    <li>Collision calendar published for Nov 15 – Dec 31</li>
    <li>Post-holiday thank-you branch for gift buyers</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Exclusions (non-negotiable)</h3>
      <ul>
    <li>Self-purchase segments from gift messaging</li>
    <li>Markets past shipping cutoff</li>
    <li>Out-of-stock gift bundles</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Metrics that prove quality</h3>
      <ul>
    <li>Gift purchase revenue</li>
    <li>Shipping deadline conversion</li>
    <li>Gift card sales from email</li>
    <li>Return rate on gift purchases</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Common mistakes</h3>
      <ul>
    <li>Gift messaging to self-purchasers</li>
    <li>Missing shipping deadline urgency</li>
    <li>No gift card last-minute option</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Holiday gifting across stack layers</h2>
  <div>
    <h3>Gift capture: Privy, Justuno</h3>
    <p>Gift intent quiz, recipient relationship, guide opt-in tags.</p>
    <p>Tags drive guide segmentation and deadline series branch.</p>
    <p><strong>Failure mode:</strong> Self-purchasers tagged gift by default.</p>
    <p><strong>Operator test:</strong> Gift vs self revenue split in Shopify reports.</p>
  </div>
  <div>
    <h3>Lifecycle orchestration: Sequenzy</h3>
    <p>Gift guide series, deadline urgency, gift card last-minute, post-gift thank-you.</p>
    <p>Dynamic shipping dates; gift card fallback module.</p>
    <p><strong>Failure mode:</strong> Replenishment email with gift guide same week.</p>
    <p><strong>Operator test:</strong> Deadline email conversion by days-to-cutoff.</p>
  </div>
  <div>
    <h3>Multichannel urgency: Omnisend, Postscript</h3>
    <p>Final 48h SMS to opted-in gift intenders.</p>
    <p>One SMS cap per season; quiet hours maintained.</p>
    <p><strong>Failure mode:</strong> Daily SMS countdown spam.</p>
    <p><strong>Operator test:</strong> Gift SMS opt-out under 2%.</p>
  </div>
  <div>
    <h3>Proof modules: Yotpo</h3>
    <p>Gift-appropriate UGC in guide emails.</p>
    <p>Unboxing and gift reaction photos in templates.</p>
    <p><strong>Failure mode:</strong> Generic product shots without gift context.</p>
    <p><strong>Operator test:</strong> Guide CTR with gift UGC vs without.</p>
  </div>
  <div>
    <h3>VIP + loyalty: Klaviyo, Marsello</h3>
    <p>Early guide access; points messaging paused during deadline week.</p>
    <p>VIP gets early access not deeper discount.</p>
    <p><strong>Failure mode:</strong> Double points + gift sale stack.</p>
    <p><strong>Operator test:</strong> VIP gift revenue vs general list margin.</p>
  </div>
  <div>
    <h3>Analytics: Shopify</h3>
    <p>Gift attribution, gift card %, return rate on gifts, deadline conversion curve.</p>
    <p>Daily dashboard Dec 10–24.</p>
    <p><strong>Failure mode:</strong> Total revenue without gift margin context.</p>
    <p><strong>Operator test:</strong> Gift return rate vs self-purchase benchmark.</p>
  </div>

      <h2>Timing and trigger governance</h2>
  <p>Gift guide: T-28 days primary holiday.</p>
  <p>Deadline reminders: T-14, T-7, T-3, T-1 by zone.</p>
  <p>Gift card push: after physical cutoff per zone.</p>
  <p>SMS final 48h: once per opted-in gift intender.</p>
  <p>Pause replenishment and winback promos for gift-tagged Dec 1–25 unless opted out.</p>

      <h2>Measurement across the stack</h2>
  <p>Gift revenue % of Q4 email attribution.</p>
  <p>Gift card sales from last-minute series.</p>
  <p>Conversion by deadline email tranche.</p>
  <p>Return rate gift vs non-gift orders.</p>

      <h2>Related playbooks</h2>
  <p>Peak: <a class="link" href="/use-cases/black-friday">Black Friday campaigns</a>.</p>
  <p>Segments: <a class="link" href="/for/jewelry">jewelry</a>, <a class="link" href="/guides/seasonal-campaigns">seasonal governance</a>.</p>
  <p>Post: <a class="link" href="/use-cases/post-purchase">post-purchase</a> gift branch.</p>

<h2>Stack coordination for holiday gifting</h2>
<p>holiday gifting is not an email template problem — it is a stack handoff problem. Trigger: Holiday calendar; gift guide engagement; shipping deadline proximity Timing: Gift guide 4 weeks out; shipping deadline reminders; last-minute digital gift cards Every layer must read the same customer state: capture tags from Privy, lifecycle execution in Sequenzy, proof modules from Yotpo, loyalty tier from Marsello, SMS consent from Postscript. When match gift timing, deadlines, and bundles, margin after discount matters more than attributed revenue.</p>
<p><strong>Gift capture:</strong> Gift intent quiz, recipient relationship, guide opt-in tags. Playbook fit: Tags drive guide segmentation and deadline series branch. Failure mode: Self-purchasers tagged gift by default. Operator test: Gift vs self revenue split in Shopify reports.</p>
